Peds Surgery is
super competitive.

76
00:04:39,462 --> 00:04:42,247
That's why I'm armed with
letters of recommendation

77
00:04:42,349 --> 00:04:45,734
to put the competition to shame.
Shepherd says I'm talented.

78
00:04:45,836 --> 00:04:48,097
Sloan finds it an
honor to work with me...

79
00:04:48,121 --> 00:04:51,489
- What does the chief think?
- I'm still working on that.

80
00:04:51,591 --> 00:04:54,776
Chief's recommendation matters.
Everyone on the committee...

81
00:04:54,878 --> 00:04:58,379
I know! You calm down.
I've got it under control.

82
00:04:58,481 --> 00:05:01,950
Good. Because
speaking on behalf of me,

83
00:05:02,052 --> 00:05:05,686
we couldn't be more
excited to have you. Yay.

84
00:05:07,824 --> 00:05:09,257
Chief? Just a friendly nudge.

85
00:05:09,359 --> 00:05:12,060
Your recommendation is
due by the end of the day.

86
00:05:12,162 --> 00:05:13,840
- I'll remind Patricia.
- You have written it?

87
00:05:13,864 --> 00:05:16,665
You'll get your recommendation.

88
00:05:18,401 --> 00:05:20,085
- I need more time.
- No.

89
00:05:20,187 --> 00:05:22,887
Don't get me wrong. I am
honored that you asked me

90
00:05:22,989 --> 00:05:24,739
over all the other residents,

91
00:05:24,841 --> 00:05:29,310
but it's not easy distilling a doctor
of your stature to 500 words or less.

92
00:05:29,412 --> 00:05:34,732
I chose you because you're the only one
to do this without screwing up. So don't.

93
00:05:36,002 --> 00:05:38,736
Make sure he planes the patio...

94
00:05:40,106 --> 00:05:43,608
- Plates the...
- We'll get him piano lessons. Yes.

95
00:05:43,710 --> 00:05:46,143
Only puddle shell... uh.

96
00:05:46,246 --> 00:05:48,947
Only public...

97
00:05:49,049 --> 00:05:52,017
Public school so he doesn't
become a snob, I know.

98
00:05:52,119 --> 00:05:54,236
But I don't have to.
You're gonna be there

99
00:05:54,338 --> 00:05:57,288
to make sure I don't
turn him into a jerk.

100
00:05:58,875 --> 00:06:00,575
We're here.

101
00:06:01,728 --> 00:06:03,744
I love just...

102
00:06:03,847 --> 00:06:05,780
I know. You love me.

103
00:06:07,217 --> 00:06:10,501
And I love you. I'll
see you in a few.

104
00:06:13,824 --> 00:06:15,122
Thank you.

105
00:06:15,224 --> 00:06:18,292
Her blood pressure's
higher than it was yesterday.

106
00:06:18,412 --> 00:06:19,772
- We can't wait.
- I know...

107
00:06:19,796 --> 00:06:22,630
You want me to be aware.
You're a good doctor. So am I.

108
00:06:22,732 --> 00:06:24,732
Let's just be good together.

109
00:06:24,835 --> 00:06:26,646
Your guy and my
guy work well together.

110
00:06:26,670 --> 00:06:29,030
My guy works well with everyone.

111
00:06:31,959 --> 00:06:33,319
- Dr. Stevens?
- Yes.

112
00:06:33,343 --> 00:06:35,443
Think we'll get to
scrub in on a surgery?

113
00:06:35,545 --> 00:06:39,181
You losers think you're capable of
holding someone's life in your hands

114
00:06:39,283 --> 00:06:43,200
when you could barely
finish the intern bowl? Really?

115
00:06:44,404 --> 00:06:47,171
- Dr. Stevens, remember me?
- Yes.

116
00:06:47,274 --> 00:06:50,625
I was here a couple of days ago,
you told me I might have cancer.

117
00:06:50,727 --> 00:06:53,812
You sent me to an oncologist,
who sent me to an immunologist,

118
00:06:53,897 --> 00:06:56,964
who then sent me to some
other ologist I never heard of

119
00:06:57,067 --> 00:07:03,221
before I set foot in this deathtrap.
80 thousand dollars in tests later,

120
00:07:03,323 --> 00:07:06,591
the only thing wrong
with me is that I'm anemic!

121
00:07:06,693 --> 00:07:08,926
- Anemic?
- My lawyer seems to think

122
00:07:09,028 --> 00:07:11,680
that someone here
mislabeled the blood.

123
00:07:11,782 --> 00:07:15,166
Switched it with someone
else's. I was told not to come here,

124
00:07:15,268 --> 00:07:18,736
but my conscience wanted to
make sure you went through the files

125
00:07:18,839 --> 00:07:21,639
of everybody who was
here at the clinic that day.

126
00:07:21,741 --> 00:07:24,342
Of course we will. I'm so sorry.

127
00:07:24,445 --> 00:07:27,529
Don't apologize to
me. I'm just anemic.

128
00:07:27,630 --> 00:07:31,299
You apologize to
that dying person.

129
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:08,965
Middle cerebral artery?

130
00:08:08,989 --> 00:08:10,821
Yes, after I connect the STA,

131
00:08:10,923 --> 00:08:13,842
- we will close.
- Baby's having spontaneous
decels.

132
00:08:13,944 --> 00:08:17,328
Mom's hypotensive. I don't
know how much they can handle.

133
00:08:17,430 --> 00:08:19,847
MCA's bleeding a bit.
It shouldn't contribute.

134
00:08:19,949 --> 00:08:22,884
Pressure's dropping. The
baby's gonna need to come out.

135
00:08:22,986 --> 00:08:25,587
- Almost done. Wait.
- Not me that can't wait.

136
00:08:25,689 --> 00:08:28,957
- The decels are getting
more frequent.
- A fetus can't handle

137
00:08:29,059 --> 00:08:31,576
three surgeries in four days.
We have to get the baby out.

138
00:08:31,678 --> 00:08:36,798
- He's too young to come out.
- Last decel lasted 30 seconds.

139
00:08:36,900 --> 00:08:38,950
Let's go. I'm taking him out.

140
00:08:39,052 --> 00:08:41,386
- Ten-blade.
- Leave the baby in.

141
00:08:44,774 --> 00:08:47,542
Done. I'm done.

142
00:08:49,112 --> 00:08:50,628
I'm done.

143
00:08:52,615 --> 00:08:55,767
You've got a minor fracture
so you won't need surgery.

144
00:08:55,869 --> 00:08:58,219
You should on your
feet within a few weeks.

145
00:08:58,321 --> 00:09:02,340
I don't know what I was thinking.
The wound wasn't healing as fast...

146
00:09:02,442 --> 00:09:05,744
Next time, you call me, John.

147
00:09:05,846 --> 00:09:08,463
Dr. Yang, explain to my patient

148
00:09:08,565 --> 00:09:10,982
what you feel I should
have done differently

149
00:09:11,084 --> 00:09:16,371
in order to avoid this
complication. Don't be shy.

150
00:09:16,473 --> 00:09:22,177
OK. Well, patients status post
minimally invasive procedures

151
00:09:22,279 --> 00:09:25,779
have been shown to have
decreased post-surgical discomfort...

152
00:09:25,882 --> 00:09:29,634
In human please, Dr. Yang.

153
00:09:31,855 --> 00:09:34,656
This surgery should have
been done laparoscopically.

154
00:09:34,758 --> 00:09:37,609
Dr. Hunt, perhaps you
can explain to Dr. Yang

155
00:09:37,711 --> 00:09:40,228
why I chose to do
the surgery this way.

156
00:09:40,330 --> 00:09:44,132
Although some doctors prefer
to use the new technology,

157
00:09:44,234 --> 00:09:46,484
there are others who
believe it's more risky

158
00:09:46,586 --> 00:09:50,271
since we can't see or move
around as much during the surgery.

159
00:09:50,373 --> 00:09:53,074
It's half a dozen either way.

160
00:09:54,628 --> 00:09:56,778
Bravo, Dr. Hunt.

161
00:09:56,880 --> 00:09:59,864
- Do you understand, John?
- Yes.

162
00:09:59,966 --> 00:10:02,383
I have no doubt you
did the right thing by me.

163
00:10:02,485 --> 00:10:07,038
Wonderful. Now, Dr. Yang,

164
00:10:07,140 --> 00:10:10,207
please take our patient to CT.

165
00:10:10,310 --> 00:10:12,610
Maybe you'll learn
something in the process.

166
00:10:12,712 --> 00:10:18,249
While I confer with Dr. Hunt
about our course of treatment.

167
00:10:22,138 --> 00:10:24,606
- I'm on a deadline.
- Sadie Harris mislabeled

168
00:10:24,708 --> 00:10:27,509
a patient's blood sample.
The clinic's getting sued.

169
00:10:27,611 --> 00:10:30,778
- Good thing Sadie no longer
works here.
- No, it's not.

170
00:10:30,881 --> 00:10:33,581
Because it isn't just her.
The interns, all of them,

171
00:10:33,683 --> 00:10:37,668
they're capable of the same mistake.
They are dangerous and they are bad.

172
00:10:37,770 --> 00:10:40,555
Don't tell me I'm overly
emotional and it isn't personal!

173
00:10:40,657 --> 00:10:44,025
Because it is personal! I've
worked so hard to teach them,

174
00:10:44,127 --> 00:10:47,595
- and... and it is personal.
- Stevens.

175
00:10:47,697 --> 00:10:50,098
I thought the same
thing about you every day

176
00:10:50,200 --> 00:10:54,218
the first year you worked here.
Know what the chief told me?

177
00:10:54,321 --> 00:10:56,303
Get out.

178
00:11:01,061 --> 00:11:03,678
You don't get much rest,
do you, Dr. Shepherd?

179
00:11:08,335 --> 00:11:12,120
- Did you hear yourself?
- Oh, my God!

180
00:11:12,222 --> 00:11:15,623
Oh, my God! I can talk!

181
00:11:15,725 --> 00:11:18,692
I know! Listen to you!

182
00:11:21,081 --> 00:11:23,581
And the baby? How's the baby?

183
00:11:23,683 --> 00:11:26,301
The baby's stable. However,

184
00:11:26,403 --> 00:11:28,820
your new labs show
that you're pre-eclamptic.

185
00:11:28,922 --> 00:11:32,657
We hoped to keep it from progressing
to this stage, but stress of surgery

186
00:11:32,759 --> 00:11:37,061
- was a lot on your body.
- So do we need to be worried?

187
00:11:39,199 --> 00:11:43,217
Come on! Dr. Shepherd, tell
me we're done being worried.

188
00:11:45,271 --> 00:11:47,455
First moment of hope
they've had in a week.

189
00:11:47,557 --> 00:11:51,059
Pre-eclampsia is serious.
You're too close to this patient.

190
00:11:51,161 --> 00:11:54,461
Stop fighting me on this. We
had a victory. Focus on that.

191
00:11:54,563 --> 00:11:59,167
We give the family all the
information. That's our job.

192
00:12:00,586 --> 00:12:03,187
- My guy won that round.
- Meredith?

193
00:12:03,289 --> 00:12:06,540
Karev, can you go get
Jen's blood test results?

194
00:12:06,642 --> 00:12:09,010
Give me a reason why I
shouldn't go to the chief.

195
00:12:09,112 --> 00:12:12,847
- The surgery was a success.
- He made a mistake in her
first surgery.

196
00:12:12,949 --> 00:12:15,850
He caused complications.
He feels responsible.

197
00:12:15,952 --> 00:12:18,085
So tell me why I
shouldn't go to the chief.

198
00:12:18,188 --> 00:12:21,256
During the trial, he lost
patients. It affected him.

199
00:12:21,358 --> 00:12:25,326
For the better, I think. He
cares more, if that's possible.

200
00:12:25,428 --> 00:12:29,146
You just have to trust him.

201
00:12:29,248 --> 00:12:30,715
OK.

202
00:12:39,376 --> 00:12:42,093
- Hey.
- Calliope.

203
00:12:42,195 --> 00:12:45,513
- I haven't seen you around.
- Well, I've been avoiding you.

204
00:12:45,615 --> 00:12:47,448
I know, it's so weird.

205
00:12:47,550 --> 00:12:50,267
You share a kiss with a
woman you've never seen...

206
00:12:50,369 --> 00:12:54,405
This is a new adventure,
one I'm so ready to take,

207
00:12:54,507 --> 00:12:58,275
for the second
time, and... Anyway.

208
00:12:58,361 --> 00:13:01,729
Do you want to go
on a date with me?

209
00:13:01,831 --> 00:13:05,266
Wait, Erica and you.
She was your first?

210
00:13:05,368 --> 00:13:08,302
- Yeah.
- Oh.

211
00:13:08,405 --> 00:13:11,589
OK. So then I guess
my answer is no.

212
00:13:11,691 --> 00:13:15,042
- I'm sorry.
- Wait. What?

213
00:13:15,144 --> 00:13:18,045
Uh... Um...

214
00:13:18,147 --> 00:13:22,016
You kissed me, out of
nowhere, in a bathroom.

215
00:13:22,118 --> 00:13:23,902
OK, this is what I try to avoid.

216
00:13:24,004 --> 00:13:29,006
You're all exploring
and experimenting and...

217
