serviceable amount of research.

233
00:14:29,652 --> 00:14:31,897
A fine addition to any program."

234
00:14:31,921 --> 00:14:34,839
Fine! He used the word "fine."

235
00:14:34,941 --> 00:14:39,843
A blank page would mean more. I
pulled off a 12-person domino surgery.

236
00:14:39,946 --> 00:14:43,814
I took out and put back
six of a dying girl's organs!

237
00:14:43,916 --> 00:14:47,385
I am Dr. Bailey. I
am better than fine!

238
00:14:48,888 --> 00:14:51,288
At least he didn't
call you a baby.

239
00:14:54,127 --> 00:14:57,228
Just a minute more, Mr. Terzian.

240
00:14:57,330 --> 00:15:00,831
Oh... Done tending
to Her Highness?

241
00:15:00,933 --> 00:15:02,366
You're tough on people.

242
00:15:02,469 --> 00:15:06,020
It's good to hold such high
standards, but this is medicine.

243
00:15:06,122 --> 00:15:09,123
- No one's perfect.
- She's stubborn and
out of touch.

244
00:15:09,225 --> 00:15:12,243
Forty years experience
means nothing?

245
00:15:12,345 --> 00:15:14,156
Not if you don't
use them correctly.

246
00:15:14,180 --> 00:15:16,931
She wants to be old
and keep operating? Fine.

247
00:15:17,033 --> 00:15:20,351
- Just keep up with medicine.
- Cristina, this is one case.

248
00:15:20,453 --> 00:15:23,537
You can't judge someone
based on one case.

249
00:15:23,639 --> 00:15:25,785
That patient deserves
to know his doctor,

250
00:15:25,809 --> 00:15:28,793
no matter whose
feelings it happens to hurt.

251
00:15:31,998 --> 00:15:36,300
Laparoscopic or open, none of
us should have made that mistake.

252
00:16:08,334 --> 00:16:12,586
You realize you're
charging one of our hospital's

253
00:16:12,688 --> 00:16:15,273
most respected
surgeons with negligence.

254
00:16:15,374 --> 00:16:17,641
Yes, sir.

255
00:16:17,743 --> 00:16:20,394
Dr. Hunt, do you agree
with Dr. Yang's assessment?

256
00:16:20,496 --> 00:16:23,464
- This is Dr. Yang's call.
- I'm asking you, Dr. Hunt.

257
00:16:23,566 --> 00:16:26,300
Campbell outranks me, sir.

258
00:16:26,402 --> 00:16:30,104
I think it would be best for you
to discuss it with her directly.

259
00:16:31,624 --> 00:16:33,391
Very well. Page Dr. Campbell.

260
00:16:33,493 --> 00:16:35,943
I want to speak to that
patient before surgery.

261
00:16:36,045 --> 00:16:37,961
Yes, sir.

262
00:16:40,850 --> 00:16:42,683
Way to take a stand.

263
00:16:44,436 --> 00:16:47,772
There he is, the legend himself.

264
00:16:47,874 --> 00:16:49,674
How are you, legend?

265
00:16:50,810 --> 00:16:53,110
Are you drunk? Should
I be worried about you?

266
00:16:53,212 --> 00:16:56,814
He's got his sense of humor
back. How's your patient?

267
00:16:56,916 --> 00:17:00,117
She's good, stable. Today's
the first day in a long time

268
00:17:00,219 --> 00:17:02,653
I remember what it feels
like to be good at my job.

269
00:17:02,756 --> 00:17:06,540
You? Come on, you're like
the Dalai Lama of surgery.

270
00:17:06,642 --> 00:17:10,711
People from all over the world come to
let you cut into them. Know what else?

271
00:17:10,814 --> 00:17:13,964
You look good doing it. I
like the facial hair, by the way.

272
00:17:14,067 --> 00:17:17,418
- Keep it that length. No more, no less.
- All right, stop.

273
00:17:17,520 --> 00:17:20,237
Derek, there's something
we need to discuss.

274
00:17:20,339 --> 00:17:22,659
- Go ahead and have sex
with Addison.
- Addison?

275
00:17:22,709 --> 00:17:24,775
- Go for it.
- I don't want to.

276
00:17:24,877 --> 00:17:27,678
Really? What did
you want to discuss?

277
00:17:32,919 --> 00:17:34,135
Nothing.

278
00:17:35,037 --> 00:17:36,871
OK.

279
00:17:43,896 --> 00:17:46,430
- How's my mother?
- Bitter.

280
00:17:46,532 --> 00:17:48,599
Angry. Genius.

281
00:17:48,701 --> 00:17:52,336
What's so wrong is how much
the chief and your mother fought.

282
00:17:52,438 --> 00:17:55,506
- Sex must have been great.
- Saying that, that's wrong.

283
00:17:55,608 --> 00:17:59,026
What's wrong? Our entire
healthcare system? I agree.

284
00:17:59,128 --> 00:18:01,345
Here it is. "March 3, 1979.

285
00:18:01,448 --> 00:18:04,148
Assisted Margaret
Campbell on a splenectomy.

286
00:18:04,250 --> 00:18:08,919
Impressive resume, adequate
technique." Hack! Even then.

287
00:18:09,021 --> 00:18:11,089
You're working with
Margaret Campbell?

288
00:18:11,191 --> 00:18:14,675
Yeah. Ye Oldy Timey thinks
she's sane enough to do surgery.

289
00:18:14,777 --> 00:18:16,172
That's what I like
about your mom.

290
00:18:16,196 --> 00:18:18,507
She wasn't Alzheimer-y
and still operating.

291
00:18:18,531 --> 00:18:22,316
Do me a favor and shoot me if I
start making mistakes on patients

292
00:18:22,418 --> 00:18:25,052
- and think it's kosher to cut.
- Sounds like Shepherd.

293
00:18:25,154 --> 00:18:27,605
- Alex.
- Please, my guy's right.

294
00:18:27,707 --> 00:18:30,191
Your guy nicked an aneurysm
and is trying to cover his ass.

295
00:18:30,309 --> 00:18:33,394
Your guy needs to shut up.

296
00:18:39,319 --> 00:18:41,752
- What happened?
- Bypass must have blown.

297
00:18:41,854 --> 00:18:45,122
- Page Addison, meet in the OR!
- I told them everything was OK.

298
00:18:45,224 --> 00:18:49,427
I don't understand. He said
the surgery was a success.

299
00:18:49,529 --> 00:18:53,697
I'll give you an update
as soon as we can, OK?

300
00:18:53,799 --> 00:18:57,301
The swelling's not going down.

301
00:18:57,403 --> 00:19:00,571
Maybe the
ventriculostomy is plugged.

302
00:19:01,607 --> 00:19:04,308
No. Damn it!

303
00:19:10,833 --> 00:19:11,932
Derek?

304
00:19:12,034 --> 00:19:15,502
I have to take out
the temporal lobe.

305
00:19:16,622 --> 00:19:18,973
- Won't that kill her?
- No.

306
00:19:19,075 --> 00:19:23,828
She could lose some speech,
memory and vocal pattern.

307
00:19:23,930 --> 00:19:28,032
The brain can rewire. I've
done it before to stop seizures.

308
00:19:28,134 --> 00:19:30,468
Have you done
it before for this?

309
00:19:32,855 --> 00:19:35,439
- I'm doing it now.
- Baby's got decels.

310
00:19:35,542 --> 00:19:37,508
What are we doing here, Derek?

311
00:19:40,613 --> 00:19:42,045
Bayonet forceps.

312
00:19:42,147 --> 00:19:45,249
What are we supposed to say?
"Shepherd's cutting out parts

313
00:19:45,351 --> 00:19:47,885
of your wife's brain.
She'll pull through?"

314
00:19:47,987 --> 00:19:51,088
Tell him the truth. Dr. Shepherd
is doing everything he can

315
00:19:51,190 --> 00:19:54,825
- to save your wife and child.
- The guy's life ended as he
knew it. Tell him that.

316
00:19:54,927 --> 00:19:56,727
Alex, just be...

317
00:19:56,829 --> 00:19:59,497
The baby's having
heart fluctuations,

318
00:19:59,598 --> 00:20:03,784
but Dr. Montgomery is taking every
precaution to avoid an early delivery.

319
00:20:03,886 --> 00:20:06,170
- And my wife?
- Dr. Shepherd is trying to get

320
00:20:06,272 --> 00:20:11,258
the bleeding under control, but we won't
know more until the surgery's finished.

321
00:20:11,360 --> 00:20:14,094
But she won't die?

322
00:20:15,882 --> 00:20:18,982
Please tell me she won't die.

323
00:20:19,085 --> 00:20:22,335
Shepherd is doing everything
to make sure your wife lives.

324
00:20:22,437 --> 00:20:24,221
She'll live?

325
00:20:24,323 --> 00:20:27,208
Dr. Shepherd is doing
absolutely everything he can.

326
00:20:27,310 --> 00:20:29,576
We should get back.

327
00:20:29,678 --> 00:20:31,912
Right. Of course. Thanks.

328
00:20:32,014 --> 00:20:35,132
- Thank you.
- Your guy sucks.

329
00:20:39,672 --> 00:20:44,908
Mr. Terzian, your scans show a change
from Dr. Campbell's original assessment.

330
00:20:45,010 --> 00:20:47,460
There was a complication
from the surgery,

331
00:20:47,563 --> 00:20:51,865
a lacerated bile duct and artery.
You'll need another surgery to repair it.

332
00:20:51,967 --> 00:20:54,401
- Is that all?
- Yes, that's all.

333
00:20:54,503 --> 00:20:56,537
Oh, thank God!

334
00:20:56,639 --> 00:21:00,106
I thought when they told me
the chief of surgery was coming,

335
00:21:00,209 --> 00:21:02,759
I was a goner for sure.

336
00:21:02,861 --> 00:21:09,800
We wanted to make you aware that it's within
your rights to request a change of surgeon.

337
00:21:09,902 --> 00:21:13,203
- Dr. Campbell's not available?
- She's available.

338
00:21:13,305 --> 00:21:16,907
No, thank you. I
choose Dr. Campbell.

339
00:21:17,009 --> 00:21:21,061
- Very well. Dr. Campbell.
- Richard.

340
00:21:24,666 --> 00:21:28,786
Sir, with all due respect, I don't think
the patient's clear on what happened.

341
00:21:28,887 --> 00:21:31,233
You heard the patient.
He wants his doctor.

342
00:21:31,257 --> 00:21:33,691
- But sir...
- Back down, Yang.

343
00:21:35,528 --> 00:21:38,546
I just need you to tell me
if it's worthy of Dr. Bailey.

344
00:21:38,648 --> 00:21:41,548
Bailey's an ass. She
doesn't listen to residents

345
00:21:41,650 --> 00:21:44,034
when they have important
information about interns.

346
00:21:44,136 --> 00:21:45,797
You're missing the
point of the exercise,

347
00:21:45,821 --> 00:21:48,939
which is to say nice
and impressive things.

348
00:21:53,646 --> 00:21:55,278
You still hang out here?

349
00:21:56,849 --> 00:22:00,034
Just say she's dependable.
Say she's selfless.

350
00:22:00,136 --> 00:22:03,237
Everything she was
until she wasn't. Just...

351
00:22:03,339 --> 00:22:05,172
You should probably go.

352
00:22:06,809 --> 00:22:09,092
Dependably selfless.

353
00:22:09,778 --> 00:22:11,895
- Thank you.
- Hm.

354
00:22:18,638 --> 00:22:20,520
Isobel Stevens?

355
00:22:29,882 --> 00:22:33,500
It's been years since I've
had you in my OR, chief.

356
00:22:33,603 --> 00:22:37,871
I seem to remember an incident
with a clamp being dropped

357
00:22:37,973 --> 00:22:39,373
into an open body cavity.

358
00:22:39,475 --> 00:22:42,092
You're never gonna let
me live that one down.

359
00:22:42,178 --> 00:22:45,763
A good teacher never lets
up on her students. Although,

360
00:22:45,865 --> 00:22:49,099
I've often wondered how the
upcoming classes learn anything

361
00:22:49,201 --> 00:22:51,601
with the way we
teach these days.

362
00:22:51,703 --> 00:22:55,673
Attendings seem more concerned
with inspiring their students,

363
00:22:55,775 --> 00:22:59,376
using encouragement
and validation and so forth,

364
00:22:59,478 --> 00:23:02,713
instead of instilling them
with the fear and shame

365
00:23:02,815 --> 00:23:06,066
that causes one to remember
anything in the first place.

366
00:23:06,168 --> 00:23:08,368
Dr. Hunt, you come
from the military.

367
00:23:08,470 --> 00:23:12,322
Wouldn't you say the rigid aspects
of your training helped you become

368
00:23:12,425 --> 00:23:15,142
- the doctor you are today?
- Yes. Very much so.

369
00:23:15,244 --> 00:23:18,612
Dr. Yang, on the other
hand, something tells me fear

370
00:23:18,714 --> 00:23:23,150
is not something you
have often faced in the OR.

371
00:23:23,252 --> 00:23:25,719
I'd appreciate any
opportunity to learn.

372
00:23:25,821 --> 00:23:29,139
Wonderful. Let us begin then.

373
00:23:29,241 --> 00:23:33,026
Tell me how you'd do a
pulmonary embolectomy.

374
00:23:33,128 --> 00:23:35,796
I'd insert a steerable
catheter into the femoral vein

375
00:23:35,898 --> 00:23:38,849
and position a fluoroscope
adjacent to the embolus.

376
00:23:38,951 --> 00:23:42,903
What would you do if the
power should suddenly go out?

377
00:23:44,757 --> 00:23:52,096
Or if you had to operate in a hospital
that couldn't afford a fluoroscope?

378
00:23:52,198 --> 00:23:55,749
It's like a calculator. Just because
there's a machine to do it for them,

379
00:23:55,851 --> 00:23:59,002
children shouldn't have
to learn simple arithmetic?

380
00:23:59,104 --> 00:24:02,506
If it would help them
avoid mistakes like this one.

381
00:24:08,764 --> 00:24:12,315
Out of my OR!

382
00:24:13,402 --> 00:24:14,968
I said get out! Out!

383
00:24:15,804 --> 00:24:18,872
This is still my OR!

384
00:24:20,859 --> 00:24:23,927
She's bleeding into the frontal
lobe. If I can stop the bleed,

385
00:24:24,029 --> 00:24:27,547
save the rest of the
brain, she'll have a chance.

386
00:24:29,868 --> 00:24:32,920
Decels are getting longer.

387
00:24:33,022 --> 00:24:38,092
- I have to
deliver the baby.
- No. Just...

388
00:24:38,194 --> 00:24:40,594
If you cut her, she'll
bleed out. I can save her.

389
00:24:40,696 --> 00:24:42,229
How?

390
00:24:46,235 --> 00:24:49,870
- I have to cut out
the frontal lobe.
- What?

391
00:24:49,972 --> 00:24:53,189
Derek, no. Stop. Derek.
You've done enough.

392
00:24:53,291 --> 00:24:55,704
Can she live without
frontal and temporal?

393
00:24:55,728 --> 00:24:58,311
- Yes.
- No, she can't.

394
00:24:58,413 --> 00:25:00,280
This baby isn't
getting any oxygen.

395
00:25:00,399 --> 00:25:03,684
You want to save Jen, you
feel you have to, but not this way.

396
00:25:03,786 --> 00:25:05,986
I can save them
both. She will live.

397
00:25:06,038 --> 00:25:09,540
Not as the person her husband
and child need her to be.

398
00:25:09,642 --> 00:25:13,293
She'll lose everything about
her that makes her human.

399
00:25:13,395 --> 00:25:16,547
- Meredith.
- Are you sure you can do this?

400
00:25:16,649 --> 00:25:20,417
- I have no choice. Bipolars.
- Baby's heart is bottoming out.

401
00:25:20,519 --> 00:25:24,238
Damn it, Derek!
This has gone too far.

402
00:25:24,339 --> 00:25:28,541
Taking the frontal lobe out, even if
she lives, you're creating a monster.

403
00:25:28,644 --> 00:25:31,094
You don't get to play God here!

404
00:25:31,196 --> 00:25:35,715
Jen is gone, but this baby
has a chance. Let her go.

405
00:25:35,818 --> 00:25:39,353
Let it go. Please, let...

406
00:25:39,455 --> 00:25:42,755
- I'm taking the baby out.
- Put down the scalpel, Addison!

407
00:25:51,017 --> 00:25:52,750
You put down the scalpel.

408
00:26:01,794 --> 00:26:05,112
- Addison, put the scalpel down.
- You put it down!

409
00:26:05,214 --> 00:26:08,998
Get off the scalpel,
Addison! Take it off!

410
00:26:12,071 --> 00:26:14,405
- Meredith...
- Do not go anywhere.

411
00:26:17,192 --> 00:26:18,992
Karev, go!

412
00:26:23,782 --> 00:26:28,101
- Derek, don't do this.
- Do not touch my patient.

413
00:26:41,800 --> 00:26:43,901
Meredith.

414
00:26:46,405 --> 00:26:49,990
Derek, look at me. You
don't have to do this.

415
00:26:50,092 --> 00:26:54,261
Jen's gone. It's too late. You
can't save her. She's gone.

416
00:26:54,363 --> 00:26:56,430
We can save the baby.

417
00:26:57,166 --> 00:27:00,184
Derek, look at me.

418
00:27:04,139 --> 00:27:08,108
Certain surgeries get
the best of all of us.

419
00:27:08,210 --> 00:27:10,544
I made a mistake.

420
00:27:10,645 --> 00:27:13,513
A careless mistake.

421
00:27:13,615 --> 00:27:15,860
And for that, I am sorry.

422
00:27:15,884 --> 00:27:18,419
But I am only human,

423
00:27:18,521 --> 00:27:20,920
as human as any of us.

424
00:27:21,022 --> 00:27:26,260
And for that, I
do not apologize.

425
00:27:28,330 --> 00:27:31,565
- Margaret, you don't have...
- No need to discuss it further.

426
00:27:31,667 --> 00:27:33,817
No need at all.

427
00:27:33,919 --> 00:27:35,902
- Chief, we need you in OR 1!
- Karev?

428
00:27:36,004 --> 00:27:39,323
Right now, sir!

429
00:27:44,263 --> 00:27:46,663
I was fired. From the Army.

430
00:27:46,765 --> 00:27:49,249
They call it an
honorable discharge,

431
00:27:49,351 --> 00:27:53,303
but they knew it was my
time, even though I didn't.

432
00:27:54,540 --> 00:27:57,457
I'm grateful to them for that.

433
00:28:14,643 --> 00:28:17,494
The baby's still in distress.
I need to take it out.

434
00:28:17,596 --> 00:28:20,564
Wait. Just wait. The
bleeding could stop.

435
00:28:20,666 --> 00:28:24,735
The baby could stabilize. If we
do a C-section now, she'll die.

436
00:28:24,837 --> 00:28:27,370
- She is dead, Derek.
- Please, just wait.

437
00:28:27,472 --> 00:28:31,608
Most of her brain is gone. For all
intents and purposes, she's dead.

438
00:28:38,451 --> 00:28:42,368
Karev, page Dr. Friedman's team.
Tell her we have a preemie on the way.

439
00:28:45,641 --> 00:28:47,574
Stop cutting.

440
00:28:52,781 --> 00:28:55,082
Why are you cutting?

441
00:28:55,184 --> 00:28:58,568
Meredith, get some more
blood. She needs more blood.

442
00:28:59,605 --> 00:29:01,938
Get more blood.

443
00:29:02,040 --> 00:29:05,392
- She needs more blood.
- No more blood, Derek.

444
00:29:09,782 --> 00:29:11,882
No more blood.

445
00:29:14,753 --> 00:29:18,689
You're smart to get it looked at, but
it doesn't look too suspicious to me.

446
00:29:18,791 --> 00:29:22,175
- Even combined with
high LDH levels?
- Oh.

447
00:29:22,277 --> 00:29:27,064
That could be caused by
anything, mono, exercise even.

448
00:29:27,166 --> 00:29:31,184
Coupled with neurological
episodes? Hallucinations?

449
00:29:33,021 --> 00:29:36,339
There we go. All done.

450
00:29:36,441 --> 00:29:39,175
You and I both see
patients do this everyday.

451
00:29:39,277 --> 00:29:42,496
They find something and
convince themselves they're sick.

452
00:29:42,598 --> 00:29:45,415
But as doctors,
you and I both know

453
00:29:45,517 --> 00:29:49,019
that it's our job to
remain worry-free

454
00:29:49,121 --> 00:29:51,449
until we have proof
that says otherwise.

455
00:29:51,473 --> 00:29:52,684
That's what you should do.

456
00:29:52,708 --> 00:29:54,757
Relax. By this time tomorrow,

457
00:29:54,860 --> 00:29:58,378
you'll be laughing at the fact
you thought anything was wrong.

458
00:30:00,365 --> 00:30:02,298
OK. Ready?

459
00:30:04,536 --> 00:30:07,320
He looks strong.

460
00:30:09,975 --> 00:30:13,660
He definitely has a chance.
Let's get him intubated.

461
00:30:13,762 --> 00:30:16,446
Placenta.

462
00:30:40,021 --> 00:30:43,824
The steroids we gave your wife
allowed your baby's lungs to mature.

463
00:30:43,926 --> 00:30:48,445
That, combined with the extra
days that Dr. Shepherd took

464
00:30:48,547 --> 00:30:51,898
to do the surgery, makes us
very hopeful that he'll survive.

465
00:30:54,269 --> 00:30:56,937
I don't understand.
She just died?

466
00:31:01,193 --> 00:31:02,826
I'm sorry.

467
00:31:05,964 --> 00:31:08,865
Yeah, I know.
You said that. Um...

468
00:31:09,968 --> 00:31:12,586
I'm asking how she died.

469
00:31:15,457 --> 00:31:20,527
Your wife's high blood pressure
caused the bypass to fail.

470
00:31:20,629 --> 00:31:24,430
That caused the bleeding
and swelling in the brain.

471
00:31:24,533 --> 00:31:28,618
Dr. Shepherd did everything he could to save
her. There was too much damage to her brain.

472
00:31:28,720 --> 00:31:33,340
That's when Dr. Montgomery
stepped in to deliver the baby.

473
00:31:36,445 --> 00:31:40,880
You said it was a routine
procedure, she would be fine.

474
00:31:40,982 --> 00:31:43,450
Then there was a complication.

475
00:31:43,552 --> 00:31:45,702
And you said you fixed that.

476
00:31:45,804 --> 00:31:48,972
But then the baby got sick,

477
00:31:49,074 --> 00:31:51,375
and that made Jen sick.

478
00:31:51,477 --> 00:31:55,161
But then you said
you fixed that, too.

479
00:31:55,263 --> 00:31:57,597
And now she's dead.

480
00:32:00,518 --> 00:32:03,936
- I'm sorry.
- Stop saying you're sorry!

481
00:32:04,038 --> 00:32:06,939
You killed her!

482
00:32:07,042 --> 00:32:11,244
You're a murderer! A murderer!

483
00:32:11,346 --> 00:32:13,463
Where's my wife?

484
00:32:15,617 --> 00:32:17,501
I want my wife!

485
00:32:18,319 --> 00:32:20,938
I want my wife!

486
00:32:23,826 --> 00:32:25,992
I want...

487
00:32:30,199 --> 00:32:32,833
I want...

488
00:32:36,288 --> 00:32:38,421
I know it's bad. But I tried.

489
00:32:38,524 --> 00:32:43,026
You're just very complex,
and word-defying.

490
00:32:43,128 --> 00:32:45,311
Chief!

491
00:32:45,414 --> 00:32:47,881
That is a letter of
recommendation!

492
00:32:47,982 --> 00:32:50,382
O'Malley? You want me to
take pointers from O'Malley?

493
00:32:50,468 --> 00:32:54,738
You'd be hard-pressed to find a
better person to take pointers from.

494
00:32:54,840 --> 00:32:58,274
- Chief? Chief!
- Exactly!

495
00:32:58,377 --> 00:33:02,812
I am the chief of surgery. I don't have
time to write letters to pump your ego.

496
00:33:02,914 --> 00:33:05,248
My head of Neuro is
being called a murderer,

497
00:33:05,350 --> 00:33:08,435
I have to fire my general
surgeon 'cause she won't retire,

498
00:33:08,537 --> 00:33:11,371
interns are mixing up
blood samples in your clinic,

499
00:33:11,473 --> 00:33:15,542
and you want me to write a
recommendation so you can leave?

500
00:33:15,644 --> 00:33:18,644
Leave you? Sir, I am

501
00:33:18,746 --> 00:33:21,697
applying for a fellowship
in pediatric surgery.

502
00:33:21,799 --> 00:33:25,518
Which is not what we discussed! Do you
know how much of my time you wasted?

503
00:33:25,620 --> 00:33:27,921
The amount of work it
takes to groom someone?

504
00:33:28,022 --> 00:33:29,922
You were supposed
to become the next me!

505
00:33:30,024 --> 00:33:31,669
You wanted me to
become the next you.

506
00:33:31,693 --> 00:33:33,738
I am not your son
or your daughter.

507
00:33:33,762 --> 00:33:36,579
You don't pin all your
hopes and dreams on me, sir!

508
00:33:46,775 --> 00:33:49,359
I'm seeing Lexie.

509
00:33:49,461 --> 00:33:52,812
Sleeping with her too, but it's
more than that. We're happy.

510
00:33:52,914 --> 00:33:54,514
I'm happy.

511
00:33:59,721 --> 00:34:03,539
OK, that's... Maybe
I deserved that.

512
00:34:03,641 --> 00:34:04,924
You know what? I didn't.

513
00:34:05,026 --> 00:34:07,794
You have no right to tell
me who I can sleep with.

514
00:34:40,945 --> 00:34:42,623
You're worried
about your legacy.

515
00:34:42,647 --> 00:34:44,213
But I am not your legacy!

516
00:34:44,316 --> 00:34:48,818
And me applying to...
You are not listening to me.

517
00:34:48,920 --> 00:34:50,019
What the...?

518
00:34:50,121 --> 00:34:52,355
Oh, my goodness!

519
00:34:53,608 --> 00:34:57,194
Come on. Come on!
Come on, stop. Come on!

520
00:34:57,296 --> 00:35:00,080
Come on.

521
00:35:01,215 --> 00:35:04,484
It's done.

522
00:35:08,740 --> 00:35:10,556
That's her guy.

523
00:35:29,528 --> 00:35:32,062
I'd do a pulmonary arteriotomy,

524
00:35:32,164 --> 00:35:36,233
directly visualize the clot
and use forceps to extract it.

525
00:35:36,335 --> 00:35:40,069
That's how I'd do a pulmonary
embolectomy without a fluoroscope.

526
00:35:40,172 --> 00:35:43,406
The fact that you felt the
need to come tell me that

527
00:35:43,508 --> 00:35:47,694
tells me you're a much better
surgeon than I first thought.

528
00:35:48,947 --> 00:35:53,733
I've decided today's
surgery was my last.

529
00:35:53,835 --> 00:35:57,304
You look at me like you won't wake
up one day not that far from now,

530
00:35:57,406 --> 00:36:01,174
so much faster than
you can imagine,

531
00:36:01,276 --> 00:36:03,726
and find that you are me.

532
00:36:03,828 --> 00:36:07,497
When you can't cut anymore,

533
00:36:07,599 --> 00:36:09,849
what will you have?

534
00:36:09,951 --> 00:36:12,819
I was a god.

535
00:36:12,921 --> 00:36:16,923
In this OR. Holding a scalpel.

536
00:36:17,025 --> 00:36:18,892
I was a god.

537
00:36:19,861 --> 00:36:21,895
And now...

538
00:36:26,551 --> 00:36:29,469
What will you have?

539
00:36:45,870 --> 00:36:48,471
I don't see anyone
burning the place down.

540
00:36:48,573 --> 00:36:49,939
That's how they do it.

541
00:36:50,041 --> 00:36:53,143
Do everything right. As soon as
you look away, they screw it up.

542
00:36:53,245 --> 00:36:56,812
Hey, I'm sorry. I
was busy earlier.

543
00:36:56,915 --> 00:37:00,166
With myself, I was
busy, so I'm sorry.

544
00:37:00,268 --> 00:37:01,968
Don't be.

545
00:37:02,070 --> 00:37:05,355
I called you an ass.
And you were right.

546
00:37:05,457 --> 00:37:08,541
I think I just needed to vent.

547
00:37:08,643 --> 00:37:10,354
I'm sick of this place.

548
00:37:10,378 --> 00:37:12,044
Hell, I just watched
Derek Shepherd

549
00:37:12,146 --> 00:37:15,965
beat up a man because he's
sick of it. That's the way it works.

550
00:37:16,067 --> 00:37:21,237
The patients we lose, the mistakes
we make, that's how we learn.

551
00:37:21,339 --> 00:37:22,889
It's the only way
it's ever been done.

552
00:37:22,991 --> 00:37:27,042
Figure out a better way, and
you will be a better doctor than us.

553
00:37:27,145 --> 00:37:30,530
<i>Patients see us as gods.</i>

554
00:37:35,436 --> 00:37:38,554
- Izzie?
- <i>Or they see us as monsters.</i>

555
00:37:38,657 --> 00:37:42,876
<i>But the fact is,
we're just people.</i>

556
00:37:44,529 --> 00:37:46,496
Hi.

557
00:37:47,399 --> 00:37:49,015
OK, well, it's not broken.

558
00:37:49,117 --> 00:37:53,853
But you should ice it. Lots
and lots of ice. Goodbye.

559
00:37:55,707 --> 00:38:00,777
- I'm so sorry.
- It was worth it.

560
00:38:00,879 --> 00:38:03,546
No. It wasn't.

561
00:38:03,649 --> 00:38:06,266
Maybe a little.

562
00:38:07,569 --> 00:38:09,468
Thank you.

563
00:38:09,570 --> 00:38:11,237
<i>We screw up.</i>

564
00:38:13,842 --> 00:38:16,392
<i>We lose our way.</i>

565
00:38:24,269 --> 00:38:27,437
- I have experience to give.
- Calliope?

566
00:38:27,539 --> 00:38:30,640
Life experience. Like I was
married. Did you know that?

567
00:38:30,742 --> 00:38:34,844
Or that I was in the
Peace Corps. Botswana.

568
00:38:34,946 --> 00:38:36,729
It convinced me to
go to med school.

569
00:38:36,831 --> 00:38:39,599
And I've experienced
the joy of cooking.

570
00:38:39,701 --> 00:38:44,169
I make an excellent chicken piccata, in
addition to many other delicious meals

571
00:38:44,272 --> 00:38:47,056
you'd be lucky to experience.
That you can't open your eyes

572
00:38:47,158 --> 00:38:50,843
to see that makes you
a little inexperienced.

573
00:38:52,914 --> 00:38:57,416
- Um... Calliope, this is Julie.
- Hi.

574
00:38:57,518 --> 00:39:00,120
My date.

575
00:39:04,376 --> 00:39:07,844
<i>Even the best of
us have our off days.</i>

576
00:39:13,752 --> 00:39:18,571
Letter of recommendation. Callie
told me about the chief's letter.

577
00:39:18,673 --> 00:39:22,942
I figured it was the least I can
do before getting back to LA.

578
00:39:23,044 --> 00:39:28,398
- Addison Montgomery, thank you!
- Don't thank me. Just kick ass.

579
00:39:28,500 --> 00:39:32,752
Don't make me regret writing that you
are the most promising young Peds surgeon

580
00:39:32,854 --> 00:39:35,721
I've ever had the
pleasure of working with.

581
00:39:38,960 --> 00:39:41,027
<i>Still, we move forward.</i>

582
00:39:45,183 --> 00:39:48,600
Today, you were a teacher to
someone who needed to learn,

583
00:39:48,703 --> 00:39:52,789
but you were also a bully to someone
who needed compassion. You were both.

584
00:39:52,891 --> 00:39:56,125
I wasn't a bully.

585
00:39:56,227 --> 00:39:59,179
And... I was right.

586
00:39:59,281 --> 00:40:01,280
Right.

587
00:40:01,382 --> 00:40:05,434
You're a lot like her.
Stubborn, opinionated, smart.

588
00:40:05,536 --> 00:40:10,005
Forty years from now I'll have to
pry that scalpel out of your hand, too.

589
00:40:10,108 --> 00:40:12,158
From my cold dead hands.

590
00:40:13,395 --> 00:40:15,461
You're missing the point.

591
00:40:17,832 --> 00:40:20,300
I wanna be around
40 years from now.

592
00:40:39,937 --> 00:40:45,241
<i>We don't rest on our laurels or
celebrate lives we've saved in the past.</i>

593
00:41:05,312 --> 00:41:08,931
<i>Because there's always some
other patient that needs help.</i>

594
00:41:23,381 --> 00:41:27,917
<i>So we force ourselves to
keep trying, to keep learning.</i>

595
00:41:28,019 --> 00:41:32,755
You're unmotivated,
careless, selfish, distracted,

596
00:41:32,857 --> 00:41:36,942
and pretty much the people in this
hospital I'd least trust with my life.

597
00:41:37,044 --> 00:41:41,914
But that's the way it's supposed
to be. You're interns. You're babies.

598
00:41:42,016 --> 00:41:43,265
And you're lucky to work here.

599
00:41:43,367 --> 00:41:46,002
We're all lucky because
we get to save lives.

600
00:41:46,104 --> 00:41:51,307
Every day, we get to save
lives. That's our job, and...

601
00:41:51,409 --> 00:41:55,411
It's not something a lot
of people get to do, so...

602
00:41:55,514 --> 00:41:57,613
<i>- In the hope that...</i>
<i>- </i> Let's begin.

603
00:41:57,716 --> 00:41:59,159
<i>- Maybe...</i>
- New game.

604
00:41:59,183 --> 00:42:02,051
<i>- Someday...</i>
- This is Patient X.

605
00:42:02,153 --> 00:42:05,722
She's a 29-year-old female
we misdiagnosed with anemia

606
00:42:05,824 --> 00:42:08,991
the first time she came to us.

607
00:42:09,093 --> 00:42:11,122
Let's not make the
same mistake again.

608
00:42:11,146 --> 00:42:17,099
<i>We'll come just a little bit closer to
the gods our patients need us to be.</i>
